The definition of `IsBernoulliOn` is `HasLaw X Ber(u, p) P`. The law `Ber(u, p)` is defined as the product measure of `p`-Bernoulli distributions on `u`. This means that the coordinates `i ∈ X ω` for `i ∈ u` are independent, and each has probability `p`.

